We got outrun by it.

00:03:25.304 --> 00:03:26.939 align:start size:88% position:13%
<i> (Jaye Watson)
 Young onset Alzheimer's,</i>

00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:30.176 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> meaning onset on
 or before 60 years old,</i>

00:03:30.276 --> 00:03:33.612 align:start size:94% position:6%
<i> accounts for less than
 1% of all Alzheimer's disease</i>

00:03:33.713 --> 00:03:37.216 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> thought to affect
 50 in 100,000 people.</i>

00:03:37.316 --> 00:03:41.053
<i> In 10% of young onset cases,
 there is a family history.</i>

00:03:41.153 --> 00:03:44.156
<i> A grandparent will have it,
 then their child will have it,</i>

00:03:44.256 --> 00:03:45.724
<i> then their grandchild.</i>

00:03:45.824 --> 00:03:49.328
<i> With each generation
 facing a 50% risk.</i>

00:03:49.428 --> 00:03:51.530 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> Dr. Wingo and his team
 began research</i>

00:03:51.631 --> 00:03:54.600 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> to discover the cause
 for the other 90%,</i>

00:03:54.700 --> 00:03:55.969
<i> like Cecile,</i>

00:03:56.069 --> 00:03:57.603
<i> who didn't have
 a family history.</i>

00:03:57.703 --> 00:03:59.705
<i> Although, she
 did have a gene.</i>

00:03:59.805 --> 00:04:04.776
<i> APOE e4, a variation on
 the more common APOE e3,</i>

00:04:04.877 --> 00:04:07.012 align:start size:88% position:13%
<i> which has been connected
